Parliament, Tuesday, 19 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Social Development will tomorrow be briefed by the Department of Social Development on its third and fourth quarter financial and non-financial performance report for 2018/19 financial year (July – September and October – December 2018). The department will also present its draft organogram and the expenditure patterns of the Social Worker Employment Grant per province. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 20 February 2019
	Time: 10:00 
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Ground Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE SOCIAL DEVELOPMENT, MS ROSEMARY CAPA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za Committees have the power to summons any person to appear before them to give evidence or produce documents. They may ask any person or institution to report to them and may receive petitions, representations or submissions from the public. They play a crucial role in the law-making process.Read more